  "text": "The Kafka consumer heartbeat session timeout is defined and handled in three key files:\n\n1. **GroupRebalanceConfig.java** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/GroupRebalanceConfig.java) - Defines the session timeout configuration:\n   - Line 41: Public field `sessionTimeoutMs` stores the heartbeat session timeout threshold\n   - Line 52: The configuration is read from `CommonClientConfigs.SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG`\n\n2. **Heartbeat.java** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/Heartbeat.java) - Manages the heartbeat session timeout timer:\n   - Line 52: Creates a session timer with `time.timer(config.sessionTimeoutMs)`\n   - Line 119-122: The `sessionTimeoutExpired()` method checks if the session timeout has expired by calling `sessionTimer.isExpired()`\n   - Line 102, 126, 133: The session timeout is reset upon successful heartbeat reception\n\n3. **AbstractCoordinator.java** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/AbstractCoordinator.java) - Raises/logs the timeout during consumer polling:\n   - Line 1513: In the heartbeat thread's polling loop, checks `heartbeat.sessionTimeoutExpired(now)` to detect if the session timeout has been exceeded\n   - Line 1516-1517: When timeout is detected, calls `markCoordinatorUnknown(\"session timed out without receiving a heartbeat response\")` to handle the timeout\n   - Line 1006-1008: The `markCoordinatorUnknown()` method logs the timeout message: \"Group coordinator {} is unavailable or invalid due to cause: {}\" with the cause being \"session timed out without receiving a heartbeat response\"\n\nThe flow is: Consumer's configuration defines `sessionTimeoutMs` → Heartbeat class creates and monitors the session timer → AbstractCoordinator checks `sessionTimeoutExpired()` during polling loop → When expired, logs the error and marks coordinator as unknown, causing the consumer to drop membership and attempt to rediscover the coordinator."
}

